{
  "format_version": 1,
  "name": "annales",
  "record": {
    "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
    "description": "One reading in a log — the `data` half of a series line (§5.4).\n\nThe reading's key (its date) and its `refs` ride in the envelope, and its home,\ncore, kind, and series name are the file's location and name (I3), so none of\nthem is stored here. What is left is what a hand actually gave: the positional\nvalues it typed, and an optional note.\n\nValues stay strings on disk. A weight is `\"78.4\"`, not a float that a JSON\nreader might round or reformat — a record is read by hand as often as by code\n(I6, I8), and Annales logs prose as readily as numbers.",
    "properties": {
      "note": {
        "description": "A hand's remark on this reading.",
        "type": [
          "string",
          "null"
        ]
      },
      "values": {
        "description": "What was read, in the order it was given. Empty for a line whose whole\ncontent is its references — a \"where you've been\" fact is its `mappa:` ref.",
        "items": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "type": "array"
      }
    },
    "title": "LogReading",
    "type": "object"
  },
  "tokens": [
    {
      "named": true,
      "shape": "series",
      "token": "log"
    }
  ]
}
